ith heat exchanger\\r\\nDrive Type: Sail drive\\r\\nPropeller: Fixed propeller with rope cutter\\r\\nMaximum Speed: 9 knots, 7 under power\\r\\nControl panel close to helmsman, with tachometer. \\r\\nEngine is accessible from front and both sides for service. Professionally serviced every year from new.\\r\\n\\r\\nFresh Water Tanks: 2  (265 Litres)\\r\\nFuel Tank: 1  (90 Litres)\\r\\n\\r\\nExtensive tool kit\\r\\nVolvo engine spares (water impellor, alternator belt, oil filter)<br>\",\"navigation\":\"Electronics\\r\\nRaymarine ST60 Tridata (depth\\/speed\\/distance and temp)\\r\\nRaymarine ST60 Wind speed and direction\\r\\nRaymarine C70 colour chartplotter with radar overlay and AIS receiver\\r\\nRaymarine ST6001 Autopilot (built-in with fast-rate gyro upgrade)\\r\\nPedestal mounted steering Compass (and grab-rail over)\\r\\nRaymarine 54E fixed VHF with masthead aerial\\r\\nNasa Navtex with USB PC connection\\r\\nUpgraded Sony FM Radio\\/CD player\\r\\n\\r\\nMedical kit\\r\\nEntel hand held VHF with 12v charger\\r\\n\\r\\nNavionics Gold XL chartplotter card\\r\\nAdmiralty leisure chart folios for Channel areas\\r\\nImray charts for Brittany\\r\\nPilot books for Channel and N France (+ Reeds)\\r\\nFCC marine chronometer and barometer\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nOutside Equipment\\/Extras\\r\\nTeak cockpit seats and toerail\\r\\nCockpit table\\r\\nSwimming ladder\\r\\nCockpit shower\\r\\nOutboard engine bracket\\r\\nLiferaft (Seago 4 man cannister)\\r\\nBosun&#146;s chair\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nElectric windlass upgraded with additional rope gypsy, 40m calibrated chain, 16kg CQR and 2nd bow roller.\\r\\n\\r\\nSafety Equipment\\r\\n&#149;\\t4 man life raft in cannister mounted in transom well\\r\\n&#149;\\t4 life jackets with safety harnesses\\r\\n&#149;\\t4 safety lines\\r\\n&#149;\\tDanbuoy with named horseshoe lifebuoy and light\\r\\n&#149;\\tOscar MOB rescue sling + block and tackle\\r\\n&#149;\\t3 folding padeyes in cockpit (for lifeline attachment)\\r\\n&#149;\\tWebbing jackstays x 2 \\r\\n&#149;\\tMasthead tricolour and anchor lights\\r\\n&#149;\\tDeck-level navigation lights plus steaming light\\r\\n&#149;\\tRadar reflector\\r\\n&#149;\\tGas alarm\\r\\n&#149;\\tSmoke alarm\\r\\n&#149;\\tFog horn\\r\\n&#149;\\tProp-mounted Rope cutter\\r\\n&#149;\\tHeavy-duty rigging cutter\\r\\n&#149;\\tFire extinguishers x 3\\r\\n&#149;\\tComprehensive manuals including Volvo workshop manua\\r\\n\\r\\nDeck Fittings and Fixtures\\r\\n&#149;\\tTeak handrails on coachroof. Teak toerails on hulldeck joint. \\r\\n&#149;\\tSelf-draining chain locker with eye bolt and integrated windlass bracket, cover with locking bolt. \\r\\n&#149;\\tStemhead fitting with anchor roller. Second bowroller fitted.\\r\\n&#149;\\tS\\/S bow protector fitted.\\r\\n&#149;\\tPulpit in two separate parts with separate green\\/red navigation lights. \\r\\n&#149;\\tAsymmetrical spinnaker tack ring ahead of forestay. \\r\\n&#149;\\tPushpits with horseshoe buoy holder, flag pole holder and opening cable gate with hooks. \\r\\n&#149;\\tStanchions with 2 levels of stainless steel guard-rails. \\r\\n&#149;\\t4 Mooring cleats and 2 spring cleats with stainless steel rubbing plates on sheer line. \\r\\n&#149;\\tSingle chainplate for cap shrouds\\/aft lower shrouds including eyes for fixing halyards. \\r\\n&#149;\\t2 deck filler plates for water, 1 for fuel. \\r\\n&#149;\\tMainsheet track on cockpit sole with adjustable traveller. \\r\\n&#149;\\tGenoa sheet track with piston lead blocks. \\r\\n&#149;\\t2 x sheet turning blocks with built-in jammers\\r\\n&#149;\\t2 x spinnaker sheet blocks. \\r\\n&#149;\\tAluminium mast step with return blocks. \\r\\n&#149;\\tStainless steel swan neck for electric cable gland. \\r\\n&#149;\\t2 x 5 sheave deck organizers for halyard returns to cockpit. \\r\\n&#149;\\t8 clutches on coachroof. \\r\\n&#149;\\t2 x upgraded Harken ST40 halyard winches on coachroof. \\r\\n&#149;\\t2 x Harken ST40 Genoa sheet winches on coamings close to helmsman. \\r\\n&#149;\\t2x Harken winch handles and 3x winch-handle pockets\\r\\n&#149;\\tClutches on toerail for Genoa furling line and asymmetric spinnaker tack line. \\r\\n&#149;\\tSliding companionway hatch and washboard in Plexiglas with stops and lock. \\r\\n&#149;\\tStowage for washboard behind aftcabin door. \\r\\n&#149;\\tLarge opening hatch over main saloon\\r\\n&#149;\\t2 x opening hatches above forecabin\\r\\n&#149;\\t1 x opening hatch over heads compartment\\r\\n&#149;\\t1 x opening hatch over aft cabin and opening portlight\\r\\n&#149;\\t2 x opening portlights (main saloon)\\r\\n&#149;\\t2 x fixed portlights and 2 x hull portlights (main saloon)\\r\\n&#149;\\t4 x roller hatch blinds and 4 x cream curtains with tie-backs\\r\\n\\r\\n8x fenders (4 new) \\r\\nMooring ropes\\r\\nShore lines\\r\\nBoat hook\\r\\nEnsign + staff\\r\\nAnchor ball and cone\\r\\nKedge anchor with 5m chain, 30m warp\\r\\nMisc cleaning and polishing materials<br>\",\"accomodation\":\"Accommodation\\r\\nNumber of double berths: 2 in two cabins + 2 single saloon berths with lee cloths.\\r\\nSaloon table has two drop down leaves and central drinks compartment.\\r\\nForecabin has two hanging lockers; the aft cabin has one. Both cabins have foot lockers.\\r\\nHeads with shower and electric pump. There is a small hanging locker as well as hooks for wet oilies to dry. Wash basin with storage under and easy access to seacocks.\\r\\n2 mirrors with additional storage behind\\r\\n\\r\\nInterior Equipment\\/ L-shaped Galley\\r\\nHot and cold pressurised water (heated by engine or mains 240v).\\r\\nENO 2-burner stove with oven, gimballed with panholders, and 2 Propane gas bottles.\\r\\nTwin s\\/s sinks and chromed mixer tap with cream-coloured Corian worktop and splashback.\\r\\n12v Refrigerator with additional light over. Ventilated lockers for stowage and swing-out bin.\\r\\n\\r\\nElectrical Equipment and Chart Table\\r\\nEberspacher Heating with 4 outlets (with thermostatic and\\/or timer control)\\r\\nShore power inlet with trip switch and 2 long shore leads, 1 with electricity meter\\r\\nBattery charger (multi-stage) + engine battery and 2 service batteries + alternator\\r\\nComprehensive control panel with 12v and 240v switches, also voltmeter and diesel fuel gauge Electric bilge and shower pumps (also Manual bilge pump operated from cockpit)\\r\\n\\r\\nForward facing chart table with seat, stowage under for charts with numerous lockers and cubbyholes for storage. Flexible chart table light with switchable red or white light.\\r\\n4x 240v sockets, 2x 12v sockets. Also additional heavy duty 12v socket in cockpit suitable for dinghy inflator.\\r\\n\\r\\n17&#148; widescreen 12v LCD TV with Glomex masthead aerial (analogue and digital tuners\\r\\n\\r\\nSun awning\\r\\n\\r\\nCrockery, cutlery, glassware (both breakable and unbreakable) for 6 persons\\r\\nMats, non-slip mats, coasters\\r\\nKettle, small pressure cooker, pots and pans, galley utensils\\r\\n240v kettle and toaster\\r\\nS\\/S insulated cafetiere\\r\\nChopping board to fit over sink\\r\\nInterior cleaning materials\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nInterior detail\\r\\n&#149;\\tAll joinery work in prime choice light Moabi mahogany, with fiddles and mouldings in solid wood. There are ample Moabi shelves and grab-rails throughout.\\r\\n&#149;\\tLocker doors have ventilation louvers. \\r\\n&#149;\\tThe cabin doors have double anti-vibration bolts. \\r\\n&#149;\\tCabin mattresses and saloon cushions have removable covers. \\r\\n&#149;\\tThe upper cabin and saloon linings are in Moabi wood.\\r\\n&#149;\\tRoller blinds for deck hatches\\r\\n&#149;\\tBreathable matress underlay (for improved ventilation) in both cabins\\r\\n&#149;\\tEberspacher 4 outlet heating\\r\\n&#149;\\tBlue alcantara saloon cushions &#150; smart and hard-wearing.<br>\",\"owners_comments\":\"I&nbsp;have owned the boat from new &amp; VAT was paid.&nbsp;The boat&nbsp;has not been raced or chartered. We have kept her at Plymouth Yacht Haven from new. \\r\\nShe has just been fully serviced, antifouled and polished so she is ready to go for the season. The marina has had a number of recent improvements including tarmaced car parks (including&nbsp; a secure car park), a new restaurant, and upgraded shower facilities. It is a 5 minute ferry ride to the Barbican area. It would be our intention to keep her there.  We have previously owned a 1\\/3 share, purchased through Yacht Fractions, in a smaller boat for 3 years and so have experience of more formal sharing arrangements\\r\\n&nbsp;\\r\\nAlthough the boat is&nbsp;a performance model she is very easy to sail and I often sail&nbsp;her single-handed. She is set up for&nbsp;fast, comfortable cruising and as a result we would want a no-racing clause in the share agreement. We would also need to be satisfied as to the experience of potential sharers &nbsp;\\r\\n&nbsp;\\r\\nPlymouth makes an ideal base for exploring the south coasts of Devon and Cornwall as well as for trips further afield to the Channel Islands, Brittany and the Isles of Scilly. Plymouth Sound is a sheltered place to sail and there are attractive anchorages to explore up the Tamar river.\\r\\n1\\/3 shares also available pro-rata if preferred.\\r\\n\\r\\n.<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.yachtfractions.co.uk\\/images\\/myrtlepics.htm\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Photos of Myrtle<\\/a><br>\",\"dinghy\":\"AX3 Bombard Aerodeck inflatable dinghy + oars\\r\\nHonda 2.3hp 4-stroke outboard engine\\r\\nPetrol can and spare diesel and water cans\\r\\n12v Electric heavy duty inflator with dedicated socket in cockpit<br>\",\"annual_costs\":\"The annual running costs are c &pound;6k (&pound;1500 per 1\\/4 share)  including &pound;4k marina fees to be paid in equal shares according to the share size.<br>\"}', NULL, 1353088119, 1353088119, '0', '0', 'NULL', NULL, '1', 'NULL'),(461, 'Bavaria 42 - Resolute Sold STC', 'NULL', '-', '-', '-', 0, 10950, 0.142857, 1, 7, '{\"beam\":\"3.99m\",\"draft\":\"1.8m\",\"keel\":\"Fin, wheel\",\"built\":\"2005\",\"lying\"