ower\\r\\n2 x double aft cabins with wardrobes\\r\\nCockpit cushions\\r\\nCockpit table\\r\\nBathing platform, swimming ladder and shower\\r\\nDeck hatch blinds\\r\\nFull galley equipment\\r\\nFull bedding \\r\\nSaloon upholstery recently recovered\\r\\n\\r\\n .<br>\",\"owners_comments\":\"I have owned the boat since virtually new and retained her on a charter management contract, she is generally in good condition and I intend to spend a reasonable budget ensuring that she is cosmetically in as good condition as possible and properly equipped for comfortable cruising. The cost of this is included in the asking price.  I intend to retain one share. A new share agreement will be supplied and discussed by the various partners. 2 shares remaining. Time booked for 2012 = 31st Jan to approx end April, rest of year is available.<br>\",\"dinghy\":\"New  inflatable 2010\\r\\nNew outboard 2010<br>\",\"annual_costs\":\"To be assessed but anticipated at less than &pound;2000 per share per year<br>\"}', NULL, 1353088126, 1353088126, '0', '0', 'NULL', NULL, '1', 'NULL'),(490, 'Jouet 10.4 - Juli', 'NULL', '-', '-', '-', 0, 3000, 0.2, 1, 5, '{\"beam\":\"3.6m\",\"draft\":\"1.6m\",\"keel\":\"Fin, wheel steering\",\"built\":\"1984\",\"lying\":\"Gouvia marina, Corfu\",\"teaser\":\"Comfortable yacht with deck saloon design, 7 berths in 2 double cabins and saloon. Long running group based in Gouvia, Corfu. Big capacity engine giving relaxed long distance cruising capability under power. School holidays generally no problem  Reduced to HALF PRICE due to ill health<br>\",\"equipment\":\"Mainsail with in mast reefing\\r\\nGenoa with roller furling\\r\\nCruising chute\\r\\nStorm Jib\\r\\nRunning rigging mostly dates to 1997\\r\\nStanding rigging replaced 1997 and upgraded to 8mm with swage fittings\\r\\nLewmar genoa winches\\r\\nHalyard and control winches<br>\",\"engine\":\"Perkins 4108, 50hp Diesel\\r\\nFuel capacity 165 litres\\r\\nEngine overhauled 2008 with major service of injector pump, gearbox and starter motor. New uplift pump. Recent alternator with spare.\\r\\n2 batteries\\r\\nCharging by alternator and 240v intellegent charger\\r\\nShore power and 6 outlets<br>\",\"navigation\":\"Steering compass\\r\\nHand held compass\\r\\nAutopilot\\r\\nLog\\/speed\\/depth\\r\\nWind speed and direction\\r\\nGPS and chart plotter\\r\\nVHF\\r\\nICOM hand held VHF x 2\\r\\nEPIRB\\r\\nFM radio\\r\\nWeatherfax\\r\\n4 man liferaft serviced 2008\\r\\nDanbuoy\\r\\nHoreshoe\\r\\n6 lifejackets - some auto\\r\\nHarnesses\\r\\nFlares\\r\\nfog horn\\r\\nFire extinguishers\\r\\nFire blanket\\r\\nGas alarm\\r\\nSmoke alarm\\r\\nManual and electric bilge pumps\\r\\nDelta plough main anchor 35lbs and 50m chain plus warp\\r\\nDanforth kedge anchor 15lb with warp\\r\\nElectric anchor windlass\\r\\nWarps and fenders<br>\",\"accomodation\":\"Forecabin with twin V or double\\r\\nSaloon with double converted from dinette and pilot berth\\r\\nDouble aft cabin\\r\\nHeads with electric WC, shower and wash basin\\r\\nHolding tank 80 litres\\r\\nHot water from engine and shore power\\r\\nPressurised hot and cold water\\r\\nGalley with oven and 4 burners, fridge, ice box.\\r\\nChart table<br>\",\"owners_comments\":\"Juli is very clean and well maintained vessel in a good seaworthy condition. She is extensively equipped for comfort, safety and enjoyable holidays. We have always tried to purchase good quality equipment and have installed a good battery charging regime and instruments. Juli is a comfortable holiday vessel &amp; that\'s why we chose her.  Most groups can cope with a week on a small boat but for a harmonious two week holiday, the extra space, equipment and comfort a motor sailer provides, makes the venture more relaxing. Her real strength is when two couples share the boat. The small double in the aft cabin is a bit cosy but avoids disturbing the main saloon to make up the saloon double berth.\\r\\n\\r\\nWe meet up when we can and staying together on Juli (even for a work week) gets everyone onside. You can discuss\\/ plan and leave with joint expectations.\\r\\n\\r\\nMembers make use of the vessel for their holidays and can invite family and friends of their choosing as crew. Good documentation aboard and members willing to assist smooth introduction of membership.\\r\\n\\r\\n\\r\\nIt is worth mentioning the holiday rota - really in fifteen years this has never been a problem. 1st 2 week choice goes down the list. 2nd 2 week choice goes up the list. The following year, the person at the top of the list goes to the bottom everyone else moves up and repeat. That done, swaps often take place but no offence is taken if adjustments cannot be made (not sure if rare or never failed to resolve members hopes). We cope with sons and daughters &amp; grandchildren at school, university, weddings etc. never have been a problem. As August is often avoided for those without children (cheaper flights at other times) I cannot see  school holidays time as being a problem for those who require such periods but all existing members would need to have reached this understanding\\r\\n\\r\\nWhat the syndicate will be looking for in a new member is another like minded person with some boating experience (new members require insurance approval), common sense and with a natural caution of the sea. \\r\\n\\r\\nWe expect that a new member may need some help. In Mediterranean ports and marinas it is all about close quarter manoeuvres. All current and previous members have needed some help with this aspect so there will be some offers and possibly generous ones of first time, onboard, help.\\r\\n\\r\\nThere are peak season holiday periods in 2012 available for a new member.School holidays generally. Reduced to HALF PRICE due to ill health\\r\\n\\r\\nNo Smoking permitted on board<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.yachtfractions.co.uk\\/images\\/julipics.htm\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Photos of Juli <\\/a>and<a href=\\\"http:\\/\\/www.yachtfractions.co.uk\\/images\\/corfupics.htm\\\" target=\\\"_blank\\\">Photos of Corfu, surrounding islands and the Southern Ionian and Gouvia swimming pool<\\/a><br>\",\"dinghy\":\"Avon 2.5m Aerodeck\\r\\nMariner 4hp outboard<br>\",\"annual_costs\":\"We plan a budget of &pound;300 per Quarter per Share. The two biggest expenses are the mooring at Gouvia and insurance. Approximately, on average 2\\/3 of contributions are spent on expenses including minor emergency renewals, for example, renewing failed equipment such as a Ships battery or bilge pumps. The balance is then spent on either bigger but not urgent renewals or new items (recent examples Dinghy, Outboard, Life raft GPS Plotter).\\r\\n\\r\\nWe also regularly valet sails, change the engine oil every 100hrs, routinely exercise all seacock and immediately attend to any minor running repairs. pumps, cleats, running rigging, electronics etc so that Juli is always in a good, seaworthy and ready to sail condition.<br>\"}', NULL, 1353088126, 1353088126, '0', '0', 'NULL', NULL, '1', 'NULL'),(491, 'Catalac 9mtr - Floss - sale agreed', 'NULL', '-', '-', '-', 0, 5750, 0.333333, 1, 3, '{\"beam\":\"4.2m\",\"draft\":\"0.75m\",\"keel\":\"Cat\",\"built\":\"1982\",\"lying\":\"Marina nr Barcelona - see notes\",\"teaser\":\"Ionian - A well maintained cruising cat owned by a well established group. Based Preveza Marina. Open to serious realistic offers<br>\",\"equipment\":\"Mainsail in blue by Arun with slab reefing and lazyjacks\\r\\nGenoa in blue by Arun with Rotostay roller furling\\r\\nNo 1 jib\\r\\nRunning and standing rigging replaced 1998\\r\\nMainsail cover\\r\\nCockpit dodgers<br>\",\"engine\":\"Yanmar 2GM 18hp diesel with sonic outdrive\\r\\nOutdrive is connected to rudders giving greater control. Hydraulic lift to raise outdrive clear of water when sailing. \\r\\n2 x 80a\\/h batteries\\r\\n36litres fuel\\r\\nCharging from alternator and stage 2 220v\\/12v charger\\r\\nShore power and 6 outlets<br>\",\"navigation\":\"Steering compass\\r\\nST3000 autopil